  "narrative": {
    "intro": "This page covers Department of the Treasury contract obligations for FY2026 to date. Total obligations are $4.5B across 6,571 awards, with an average award size of $678K; obligations are down 48.0% year over year. The current-year total is partial because the period reported is fiscal year to date. FY2026 obligations are smaller than prior full-year totals such as $9.6B in FY21, $10.3B in FY23, and $8.6B in FY25. Procurement in FY2026 to date concentrates in a few high-dollar NAICS categories led by Nonferrous Metal (except Aluminum) Smelting and Refining at $913M and Other Computer Related Services at $892M. The top vendors in FY2026 to date include STONEX FINANCIAL LTD at $827M, ASAHI REFINING USA INC at $334M, and FCN, INC. at $183M. All figures are contract obligations; current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date).",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How has Treasury's contract spending changed this fiscal year?",
        "body": "Obligations for FY2026 to date are $4.5B, down 48.0% year over year. This FY2026 total is partial and smaller than recent full-year totals such as $9.3B in FY22 and $9.3B in FY24. The decline coincides with fewer or smaller awards on average given the average award size of $678K across 6,571 awards. Historical context shows FY25 obligations at $8.6B and FY23 at $10.3B, indicating FY2026 to date is reduced relative to those prior years."
      },
      {
        "heading": "What are the dominant contract categories and vendors in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "NAICS categories with the largest obligations are Nonferrous Metal (except Aluminum) Smelting and Refining at $913M and Other Computer Related Services at $892M, followed by Computer Systems Design Services at $419M. The largest vendors are STONEX FINANCIAL LTD at $827M and ASAHI REFINING USA INC at $334M, with FCN, INC. at $183M and several other vendors receiving significant shares. These categories and vendors together account for a substantial portion of the $4.5B in obligations recorded so far in FY2026."
      }
    ]
  },
  "faq": [
    {
      "q": "How much does Department of the Treasury spend on contracts?",
      "a": "The Department of the Treasury has $4.5B in contract obligations for FY2026 to date. These obligations are distributed across 6,571 awards with an average award size of $678K, and obligations are down 48.0% year over year. The FY2026 total is partial because the period reported is fiscal year to date."
    },
    {
      "q": "What does Treasury buy?",
      "a": "Treasury buys a mix of goods and services dominated in FY2026 to date by Nonferrous Metal (except Aluminum) Smelting and Refining at $913M and Other Computer Related Services at $892M. Other leading categories include Computer Systems Design Services at $419M, Custom Computer Programming Services at $242M, and Paper (except Newsprint) Mills at $125M."
    },
